Staunch Mamelodi Sundowns supporter and Titans assistant coach Geoffrey Toyana has been abuzz on social media over the past few weeks mocking Kaizer Chiefs fans after the Brazilians beat the to the league title last season. Because of his social media banter, Toyana sometimes receives criticism from opposition fans but says he is enjoying it as long people are not disrespectful and personal. In a candid interview with TimesLive, he talks about when he started supporting Sundowns, who are his favourite all-time and current players and what is the legacy of former coach Pitso Mosimane. He also shared his opinion on the coaching triumvirate of Manqoba Mngqithi, Rulani Mokoena and Steve Kompela, who took over from Mosimane, and what he expect from the team this season.